      "raceComments": "{\"comment\":\"3. HASSALEH shaped with promise when third over 1200m at Windsor on debut and has evidently been given time to progress since. That experience could prove decisive and she could take plenty of beating. 5. POINTE BLEU is a Blue Point filly out of Listed winner Troarn. Pedigree suggests she can make an immediate impact. 1. BAANDEE returned with a solid Chelmsford second tackling 1400m after travelling strongly and although this is tougher she remains firmly in the mix. 6. THURSDAY GIRL showed ability when fifth at Salisbury on sole appearance. Natural progress is expected and she might feature.\",\"runners\":[3,5,1,6],\"exclusive\":false}",
